    <note>Liu(2) Tingzhi [17575] His elder brother, Yuxi [17574] (or Tinggui) was a close friend of Xiang(2) Zimin [714], who was born in the same year as Yuxi. When Tingzhi and Yuxi earned the juren in 1132, Zimin was a temporary resident in Jizhou and admired Tingzhi's literary style and arranged for the marriage between Tingzhi and his niece, who had become his ward after her father, Zimin's cousin, Ziqi [17569], died in battle with the Jin in 1126. Tingzhi's 2nd wife, who would have been 21 years old if the marriage took place in 1133, had merit (according to Yang(2) Wanli) in Tingzhi's success in the jinshi exams in 1145. Yang Wanli, WJ, 122.10a-12a, 127.8b-10a (2nd wife, born Xiang, who married him at age 21 and who died in 1175 at age 63); Wang Tinggui, WJ, 46.3b-5a; Jiangxi TZ, 21.3b (juren in 1132), 122.7a (jinshi list has mingzi as Tinggui in error for brother, who had already died). CBD, 5, 3951-2.</note>
